# 📊 Tableau User Story | Sales Performance

## 📝 Introduction

This user story outlines the specifications for building two interactive dashboards in Tableau to help stakeholders—including sales managers and executives—analyze sales performance and customer behavior effectively.

---

## 📈 Sales Dashboard | Requirements

### 🎯 Dashboard Purpose  
To provide an overview of key sales metrics and trends, enabling year-over-year analysis and actionable insights into sales performance.

### ✅ Key Requirements

🔹 KPI Overview  
- Display total sales, profit, and quantity for the current and previous year.

🔹 Sales Trends  
- Show monthly trends for each KPI for both current and previous years.  
- Highlight months with the highest and lowest sales.

🔹 Product Subcategory Comparison  
- Compare sales performance by product subcategories (current vs previous year).  
- Include sales vs profit comparisons.

🔹 Weekly Trends for Sales & Profit  
- Show weekly sales and profit data for the current year.  
- Display average weekly values.  
- Highlight weeks that are above or below average.

---

## 👥 Customer Dashboard | Requirements

### 🎯 Dashboard Purpose  
To provide insights into customer trends, behaviors, and segmentation, supporting marketing and management strategies for better customer satisfaction.

### ✅ Key Requirements

🔹 KPI Overview  
- Display total number of customers, sales per customer, and total number of orders for both the current and previous year.

🔹 Customer Trends  
- Monthly trends for each KPI (current vs previous year).  
- Highlight months with the highest and lowest sales.

🔹 Customer Distribution by Number of Orders  
- Visualize customer distribution based on order frequency.  
- Gain insights into customer loyalty and engagement.

🔹 Top 10 Customers by Profit  
- Display top 10 customers by profit generated.  
- Show details like rank, number of orders, sales, profit, and last order date.

---

## 🎨 Design & Interactivity Requirements

### 🔄 Dashboard Dynamics  
- Allow users to select any desired year for historical comparison.  
- Provide easy navigation between Sales and Customer dashboards.  
- Enable interactive charts and graphs with click-based filters.

### 🧮 Data Filters  
- Filters by Product: category, subcategory  
- Filters by Location: region, state, city
